&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Company&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Redpin we&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;simplify life&#39;s most important payments.&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Buying a new property overseas can be a stressful time, especially when it comes to moving your money. Through our Currencies Direct and TorFX brands we&#39;ve been helping people do just that for over 25 years. With recent investment we&#39;re now on a mission to build a new range of digital products and services that will make moving money Internationally for Real Estate purchases even easier&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We’re on a mission to become the solution for Real Estate payments everywhere&lt;/strong&gt;. To do this, we are transitioning our business from a horizontal FX platform to a verticalized, embedded software company, as we look to the future and Redpin 2.0. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;As part of this mission, we’re thrilled to announce we are open a new office in Hyderabad! We’re recruiting for several Engineering roles covering front end (React.js) features.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re now seeking a Staff React Engineer to join the development of our product suite. You’ll play a pivotal role in creating robust, scalable, and intuitive applications that empower customers to handle Real Estate transactions including international payments with ease.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a new role, based out of our Hyderabad office. The successful candidate will be at the forefront of our new product development and will have significant opportunity to take ownership of some of our upcoming features&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Architect and develop high-quality front-end features and user interfaces using React&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with cross-functional teams (such as Product &amp;amp; Design) to integrate backend services and ensure seamless data flow&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Optimize applications for speed, scalability, and responsiveness&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead code review, maintain coding standards and contribute to continuous improvement initiatives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mentor junior developers and promote a culture of technical excellence&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay abreast of emerging technologies and propose innovative solutions to enhance our product offerings&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Need&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;8+ years of professional experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advanced React.js knowledge: Proficiency in using React hooks, context and the component lifecycle&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;State Management: Experience with state management libraries and Redux, MobX or Context API&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Modern JavaScript: Deep understanding of ES6+ features such as async/await, destructuring, etc&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Component Design: Ability to design reusable components and management component hierarchies effectively&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Performance Optimization: Skills in optimising React applications for performance, including lazy loading and memorization&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-stringify-indent=&quot;0&quot; data-stringify-border=&quot;0&quot;&gt;Experience integrating&amp;nbsp;design tokens into UI components to ensure consistent theming and styling&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-stringify-indent=&quot;0&quot; data-stringify-border=&quot;0&quot;&gt;Familiarity with design systems and tools such as Figma, Storybook, or similar
&lt;div id=&quot;message-list_1767957534.194769&quot; class=&quot;c-virtual_list__item&quot; data-qa=&quot;virtual-list-item&quot; data-item-key=&quot;1767957534.194769&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;c-message_kit__background p-message_pane

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Team:&lt;/strong&gt; Core Platform&lt;strong&gt; &lt;br&gt;Reports to: &lt;/strong&gt;Director of Engineering&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;About the Company&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Redpin we simplify life&#39;s most important payments. Buying a new property overseas can be a stressful time, especially when it comes to moving your money. Through our Currencies Direct and TorFX brands we&#39;ve been helping people do just that for over 25 years. With recent investment we&#39;re now on a mission to build a new range of digital products and services that will make moving money internationally for real estate purchases even easier. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;We&#39;re on a mission to become the solution for real estate payments everywhere. To do this, we are transitioning our business from a horizontal FX platform to a verticalized, embedded software company, as we look to the future and Redpin 2.0. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;As part of this mission, we&#39;re thrilled to announce we have opened a new office in Hyderabad!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will own the delivery of Redpin&#39;s most important cross-functional business initiatives — the programs the company is betting on — and be accountable for the outcome, not just the plan.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Success means bringing multiple teams into alignment on scope, dependencies, and timelines, holding that alignment as things change, and driving execution through to shipped. You&#39;ll operate across Engineering, Product, Operations, and the CTO&#39;s office, turning ambiguous, high-stakes goals into a plan teams believe in and then landing it. When a program starts slipping from green to yellow to red, you&#39;re the one who sees it first and does what it takes to turn it back&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;You&#39;ll do this as a nimble, async-first operator — not by filling calendars with status meetings.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own end-to-end delivery of key cross-functional initiatives across Core Platform, from planning to ship.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive quarterly planning: shape goals with leadership, decompose initiatives, map dependencies, and align teams on scope and timelines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain an honest RAG view of program health; detect risk early, escalate the right issues to the right people, and drive the actions that turn red/yellow back to green.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Unblock teams — broker decisions, remove dependencies, and make pragmatic calls rather than logging problems and waiting.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage risk and dependencies across teams and third parties (banking partners, payment rails, critical vendors).&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Keep leadership informed through crisp written updates that drive decisions without a meeting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Need&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven track record delivering complex, cross-functional technical programs in a fast moving environment.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong technical fluency — enough to earn engineers&#39; trust, reason about architecture and trade-offs, and make pragmatic decisions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;Excellent written communication and stakeholder management across ICs, managers, Directors, Product, Operations, and executive leadership; strong persuasion and influence without authority.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Sharp risk and escalation instincts — you recognise &quot;yellow turning red&quot; early and know how to intervene.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfort with ambiguity and a bias to action; async-first working style.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with quarterly/OKR planning and dependency management at scale&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
